Data Set and Project Summary¶

I am using the same data file/csv that I got from kaggle for the first project for this assignment. The change that I will be making between this assignment and the previous one, is the factor from the data that I will be analyzing. Previously we looked at the happiness score in relation to the facors. This time I will be analyzing the relationship of the cpi score to happiness score, and gdp to see if it has a significant relationship.

The cpi score is a Corruption Perception Index, which is a score from Transparency which is an organization that is dedicated to eliminating corruption within governments globally. They created the Corruption perception index to measure government corruptiona nd transparency, it is caluclated from surveys that are completed by residents of said country. It lies on a scale of 0-100, 100 meaning no corruption, 0 being the most corrupted.

The regression models I will be using for this project are correlations and anova regression models. I will create correlation matrices for the different factors that I am comparing(cpi and happiness and cpi and gdp). I will be using a pearson correlation to compare them. The pearson correlation is a ratio that compares the covariability of X and Y, in this case, either cpi and happiness or cpi and gdp with with the variability of X and Y separately. However, I also included correlation matrices from the other two types, the kendall and spearman correlation which are are used to determine correlation with in ranks. These I decided to not use for calculating my correlation coefficients because we are not looking at how the gdp or happiness is ranked in the individual countries compared to the cpi score. After this I used an anova regression model to create a deeper analysis. this is explained in that section.

Correlation exploration¶

in this section, I will run the different correlation methods of pearson, kendall, and spearman. I am using all of them to show that the correlations vary between the different formulas for sorelation but they all so similar levels of correlation whether that is negative or positive for the variables. for instance, the correlation between family and social support are very highly and negatively correlated, the value for pearson being -0.87, kendall being -0.67 and spearman being -0.86. I also printed out the list of correlations relatign to cpi scores after each matrix. The correlation type I will be using later is pearson and my reasoning for that is given in the data and project overview section of my report.

ANOVA REGRESSION¶

Instead of doing a linear regression like I did in the first project, I decided to do an anova regression insead. these are commonly used within social science fields and I learned them in both my poilitical statistics course and we briefly went over them in my psychology class that is dedicated to statistics and coding in R. Anova regressions calculate the varience within the data and regressions give the values. the steps include, creating an ols regression, then taking the anova model and creating a model from it. I printed out the values and you can see that there is a significant relationship between the happiness and cpi score because the p value is 0 which is less than .05, and same with the gdp relationship.
